to drum up support
for his side?

12:29.732 --> 12:31.324
PETER (on bullhorn):
Ladies and gentlemen,

12:31.460 --> 12:34.544
to support Pawtucket Pat,
please welcome Kid Rock.

12:36.923 --> 12:38.572
Hello, Quahog.

12:38.633 --> 12:41.501
Whenever there's a town debate
with racial overtones,

12:41.653 --> 12:44.453
-I'm there on the wrong side.
-(all cheering)

12:44.473 --> 12:46.598
Aw, crap, everybody run.
It's Adult Rock.

12:46.791 --> 12:49.008
Kid, you want to tell me why
I found your mother's

12:49.160 --> 12:51.919
best T-shirt-cutting scissors
outside in the rain?

12:51.980 --> 12:53.846
-(scoffs) I don't know.
-(sighs)

12:53.999 --> 12:57.233
Why can't you be more
like your brother, The?

13:00.930 --> 13:03.356
Rupert, I was going over
our credit card statement.

13:03.492 --> 13:06.526
There's a charge for two tickets
to<i> Tootsie</i> the musical,

13:06.620 --> 13:10.604
yet I don't remember going
to see<i> Tootsie</i> the musical.

13:10.624 --> 13:14.441
Now, I'm hoping the good news
is I'm ruining the surprise.

13:14.461 --> 13:16.369
God, I can't believe
Peter is actually winning

13:16.463 --> 13:18.371
public support
for that damn statue.

13:18.465 --> 13:20.189
And he's throwing rocks
through my window,

13:20.250 --> 13:21.448
and it's his house.

13:21.468 --> 13:23.784
-(Peter grunting)
-(heavy thud)

13:23.845 --> 13:25.286
Ugh, that rock was too heavy.

13:25.347 --> 13:28.122
Got to find something lighter.

13:28.183 --> 13:30.216
Okay, so something in between.

13:30.368 --> 13:31.792
That statue is such a disgrace.

13:31.853 --> 13:33.536
I'll tell you,
part of me wants to march down

13:33.638 --> 13:35.388
to that park
and remove it myself.

13:35.524 --> 13:37.682
Well, why don't you?
It'd be a noble act.

13:37.876 --> 13:39.484
Think of it
as civil disobedience.

13:39.677 --> 13:41.635
Disobedience?
But I'm a good boy.

13:41.738 --> 13:44.322
I obey. I always obey.
I'm a good boy who obeys.

13:44.491 --> 13:46.215
Okay, d-don't think
of it as disobedience,

13:46.234 --> 13:47.884
Forget I used that word.

13:47.986 --> 13:49.494
You're a weird guy, Bri.

13:49.687 --> 13:51.645
A weird doggy guy.

13:51.706 --> 13:54.256
PETER:
Ha! Found some medium rocks.

13:54.258 --> 13:56.059
You know what?
That's a great idea.

13:56.077 --> 13:59.153
Like not separating immigrant
children from their families.

13:59.214 --> 14:01.422
<i> (applause)</i>

14:03.418 --> 14:05.251
If you're the first one
to stop applauding,

14:05.387 --> 14:07.070
that means you're racist.

14:07.088 --> 14:09.180
<i> (applause intensifies)</i>

14:10.225 --> 14:12.433
<i> (applause continues)</i>

14:14.879 --> 14:15.928
<i> (applause stops)</i>

14:16.081 --> 14:17.580
Thanks for helping me, Stewie.

14:17.640 --> 14:18.931
All right, let's tie the rope
around the statue

14:19.084 --> 14:20.341
and tow it out of here.

14:20.360 --> 14:21.767
All right, great.
But before we begin,

14:21.862 --> 14:23.753
I'm just going to use
the park bathroom

14:23.855 --> 14:25.446
-at night.
-Stewie, no.

14:28.726 --> 14:30.118
I got a lollipop!

14:33.707 --> 14:35.039
That's great, bud.

14:42.073 --> 14:44.716
Now let's stop talking about
that lollipop and get to work.

14:49.222 --> 14:51.797
Okay, we're almost
ready to do this.

14:51.950 --> 14:53.116
Did you bring the masks?

14:53.134 --> 14:54.800
-Right here.
-What the hell is this?

14:54.895 --> 14:56.636
You said to bring masks.

14:56.788 --> 14:58.730
These are from last year's
charity ball at the Guggenheim.

14:58.923 --> 15:01.140
Whatever. Just help me
tie this rope to the car.

15:01.234 --> 15:03.384
Sorry, I need a free hand
to hold up my mask.

15:03.486 --> 15:05.528
Enough with the damn masks!

15:12.395 --> 15:14.537
All right, let's get this statue
out of here.

15:28.285 --> 15:31.578
I guess you only paid
for driver's side airbags.

15:31.640 --> 15:35.016
Yeah. When I bought this, I was
dating a girl I didn't like.

15:41.942 --> 15:43.666
Wow, look at this.

15:43.726 --> 15:45.944
The statue's disappearance
is being covered everywhere.

15:46.095 --> 15:47.670
I can't believe
we really did it.

15:47.689 --> 15:49.522
-I just hope
we don't get caught.
-So what?

15:49.616 --> 15:52.008
Mom would just ground us
and take away screen time,

15:52.068 --> 15:54.786
and then realize that without
screens, she has to entertain us

15:54.937 --> 15:56.270
and immediately give it back.

15:56.331 --> 15:58.698
Stewie, destroying
a statue is a felony.

15:58.808 --> 16:00.199
If we're caught,
we'll go to prison.

16:00.293 --> 16:02.201
Prison?!
I can't go to prison.

16:02.353 --> 16:04.704
Peter watched
all six seasons of<i> Oz</i>

16:04.798 --> 16:06.372
with me in a Babybjörn.

16:06.524 --> 16:09.283
I'm too young to have
someone go poo on my face.

16:09.386 --> 16:13.179
Well, there's really
no good age for it to happen.

16:16.977 --> 16:18.810
All right, Stewie, just relax.

16:18.961 --> 16:21.037
And don't do that weird,
nervous laugh you do

16:21.097 --> 16:22.872
-when you're hiding something.
-Got it.

16:22.890 --> 16:26.058
-Morning, everybody.
-Where have you guys been?

16:26.194 --> 16:27.819
(cackles)

16:28.012 --> 16:29.136
No-Nowhere, of course!

16:29.197 --> 16:30.713
(quietly):
Will you calm down?

16:30.732 --> 16:32.381
So, uh, where's Peter?

16:32.400 --> 16:34.900
Uh, he went to some rally
'cause the statue's gone.

16:35.053 --> 16:39.146
He's angrier than Al Pacino's
forehead liver spots.

16:39.165 --> 16:41.240
Comb your hair down
instead of up.

16:41.334 --> 16:43.501
Give us some shade.
We're dying up here.

16:43.652 --> 16:45.152
Yeah, what do you call
that haircut?

16:45.171 --> 16:46.653
You're nearly 80 years old.

16:46.789 --> 16:48.506
You look like the kid
from<i> Jerry Maguire.</i>

16:48.699 --> 16:51.342
What are you going for
with all of these spots?

16:51.494 --> 16:53.919
I want to look like
mashed potatoes,

16:54.055 --> 16:56.088
with the skins on.

16:56.224 --> 16:58.391
(indistinct chatter)

17:10.387 --> 17:12.104
This is awesome.
What a turnout.

17:12.198 --> 17:14.014
And look, here comes Fox News.

17:14.075 --> 17:16.850
(horn playing "Dixie")

17:16.911 --> 17:19.370
It's amazing how recently
that show aired.

17:19.563 --> 17:22.523
That statue was a travesty
and so is the brewery.

17:22.584 --> 17:24.858
They should close it
and make juice instead.

17:24.919 --> 17:26.269
What?
How dare you?

17:26.329 --> 17:28.046
Juice will not replace us.

17:28.197 --> 17:29.955
(chanting):
Juice will not replace us!

17:30.091 --> 17:32.108
Juice will not replace us!

17:32.126 --> 17:33.551
My God, Peter,
what are you doing?

17:33.702 --> 17:36.554
Taking up politics
to avoid intimacy with my wife.

17:36.747 --> 17:38.222
Peter, is that you?

17:38.415 --> 17:40.707
(gasps) I thought
we could protest together.

17:40.727 --> 17:43.619
All right, no more politics.
Time for trains in the basement.

17:43.679 --> 17:46.289
-MAN: Stop!
-Collaborate and listen.

17:46.349 --> 17:48.232
We are from
the Narragansett tribe,

17:48.425 --> 17:51.385
from whom Pawtucket Pat
stole his recipe.

17:51.488 --> 17:55.556
And we are annoyed that no one
has asked us what we think.

17:55.617 --> 17:58.484
You guys kind of dress
like weekend Jay Leno.

17:58.620 --> 18:02.655
Thank you. We've just come
from the Wang-Holder wedding.

18:02.791 --> 18:03.989
(laughs)
See?

18:04.084 --> 18:05.808
Little more of that,
John Oliver,

18:05.827 --> 18:07.919
and maybe you'll finally
get that 14th Emmy.

18:08.088 --> 18:09.736
Well, what do you guys think?

18:09.756 --> 18:12.239
This statue is only the tip
of the iceberg.

18:12.300 --> 18:15.151
The pressing issue isn't
what someone did 300 years ago,

18:15.253 --> 18:17.578
it's how do we help
Native Americans today

18:17.597 --> 18:21.248
and end the institutional racism
that still plagues society?

18:21.267 --> 18:23.059
The poverty rate
on reservations...

18:24.128 --> 18:26.771
Oh, damn, you got sunflowered.

18:26.922 --> 18:28.106
Everyone, come back.

18:28.299 --> 18:30.333
Uh, come back.
he makes a good point.

18:30.351 --> 18:33.594
We've all been so focused
on what the statue means to us

18:33.613 --> 18:35.020
we didn't even stop to consider

18:35.115 --> 18:37.264
how Pawtucket Pat
affected others.

18:37.358 --> 18:39.008
But Pat's the town hero.

18:39.068 --> 18:41.694
If he's nothing,
then so is Quahog.

18:41.846 --> 18:44.196
-(indistinct chatter)
-No, it's not.

18:44.290 --> 18:47.125
Quahog is still
a wonderful town.

18:47.318 --> 18:49.627
I-I mean, we still got
one of those Arby's signs.

18:49.820 --> 18:52.463
You know? T-The old ones,
you know, with the big old hat?

18:52.656 --> 18:54.632
That's been gone for ten years.

18:54.825 --> 18:56.968
Oh, (bleep) this place.

18:57.161 --> 18:58.785
No, no, you know what?
No.

18:58.847 --> 19:00.546
Quahog is a wonderful town,

19:00.640 --> 19:03.866
because of who we are
and what we do,

19:03.926 --> 19:07.961
not because of some guy
who stole beer 300 years ago.

19:08.022 --> 19:10.130
Especially when
he did horrible things

19:10.191 --> 19:12.132
to some of our fellow citizens.

19:12.193 --> 19:14.727
Yeah, I guess you're right.

19:14.821 --> 19:16.045
Thank you, Peter.

19:16.063 --> 19:17.804
Now, crowd of angry whites,

19:17.866 --> 19:21.492
I think we all owe our Native
American friends an apology.

19:21.685 --> 19:23.052
ALL:
Sorry.

19:23.154 --> 19:24.887
Angry whites.

19:24.947 --> 19:27.314
-ALL: Sorry!
-That's better.

19:27.333 --> 19:30.150
Well, Brian, I guess
I owe you an apology, too.

19:30.211 --> 19:31.836
You were right from the start.

19:32.029 --> 19:33.654
Sorry things got
so heated between us

19:33.756 --> 19:35.731
and that I took a dump
in your dog food.

19:35.791 --> 19:38.342
-Wait, what?
-I know. Politics, huh?

19:38.535 --> 19:42.180
-Come on everybody,
let's go home.
-I'll drive.

19:44.875 --> 19:47.018
Where the hell are we?

19:54.585 --> 19:56.009
Good evening, I'm Tom Tucker.

19:56.070 --> 19:58.437
Our top story:
the statue of Pawtucket Pat

19:58.589 --> 20:00.773
was found earlier today
in the Quahog River.

20:00.867 --> 20:03.517
In the spirit of compromise,
the town has decided

20:03.536 --> 20:05.852
that it will be
relocated to the Quahog Museum,

20:05.955 --> 20:07.521
where it will be both remembered

20:07.540 --> 20:09.523
and never seen
by anyone ever again.

20:09.626 --> 20:12.451
Well, thank God this whole
controversy is behind us.

20:12.587 --> 20:15.046
Yeah. And Peter, I'm glad
you came to your senses.

20:15.197 --> 20:18.123
Me, too. You know, we might
even win an award for this.

20:18.218 --> 20:20.218
-Really?
-Yeah, award voters love it

20:20.386 --> 20:21.886
when someone
with a right-leaning viewpoint

20:22.055 --> 20:23.537
admits they're wrong.

20:23.556 --> 20:24.947
They declare
it's good storytelling

20:25.007 --> 20:26.224
and character development.

20:26.417 --> 20:28.226
Ooh, like<i> Three Billboards.</i>

20:28.419 --> 20:30.453
-And<i> Green Book.</i>
<i> -Driving Miss Daisy.</i>

20:30.513 --> 20:32.063
<i> American History X.</i>

20:32.256 --> 20:33.898
Yeah, all those.
And many more.

20:34.091 --> 20:37.050
But can anyone name a single
movie where someone on the left

20:37.111 --> 20:40.796
took on a more
Republican-leaning viewpoint?

20:40.856 --> 20:42.815
Doesn't even have
to have won an award.

20:42.909 --> 20:44.951
Just has to exist.

20:46.788 --> 20:48.487
Anyone?

20:48.581 --> 20:50.656
Anything?

20:50.750 --> 20:53.918
What about Fritz Lang's
<i> Metropolis?</i>

20:54.111 --> 20:55.311
How'd you get here?

20:55.371 --> 20:58.572
Mm, in my Hyundai Sonata.

20:58.633 --> 21:00.299
(shudders)

